-- Avtotor Seeks $3 Billion Kaliningrad Car Project, Vedomosti Says
-- B y   Y u l i y a   F e d o r i n o v a
-- 2012-05-28T04:14:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-28/avtotor-seeks-3-billion-kaliningrad-car-project-vedomosti-says.html
Avtotor, a closely held Russian car
manufacturer, wants to start 100 billion rubles ($3 billion)
project in its home Kaliningrad region to produce 350,000 cars a
year by 2018,  Vedomosti  said today, citing Avtotorâ€™s chairman
Vladimir Sherbakov.  Avtotor may set up joint ventures with international car-
makers, including Bayerisce Motoren Werke AG and  General Motors
Co. (GM)  to produce cars and auto parts, newspaper said. The partners
may take stakes of between 30 percent and 50 percent in the
ventures.  Avtotor and its partners will provide as much as 80 billion
rubles for the project, while Russian government may help to
fund it with between 20 billion rubles and 25 billion rubles,
Vedomosti said citing Sherbakov.  To contact the reporter on this story:
